<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-657] FuzzyQuery should not be final</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-657</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;I am trying to extend the FuzzyQuery to further filter the TermEnum. (I am indexing stem forms and original forms, but I only want to match original forms with a fuzzy term, otherwise I get to much noise). However, FuzzyQuery is a final class and I cannot extend it.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As discussed in the mailing list (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.gossamer-threads.com/lists/lucene/java-dev/38756&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot;&gt;http://www.gossamer-threads.com/lists/lucene/java-dev/38756&lt;/a&gt;), we want to make the private variables and inner classes protected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am attaching a patch for FuzzyQuery.java that implements this. I ran all unit tests and they passed without errors.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Andreas.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;all platforms&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
